        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 6:44PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms
developing over Davie County, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 45 mph. Frequent lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, High Point, Lexington, Thomasville, Kernersville,
Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Huntsville, and Linwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
